1
00:00:05,073 --> 00:00:09,783
The word 'atma'
is defined variously.

2
00:00:10,523 --> 00:00:14,523
So, let's use the general
term 'self'.

3
00:00:14,942 --> 00:00:18,942
Atma | Conception of Self

4
00:00:19,226 --> 00:00:21,106
So, it's been pointed out...

5
00:00:21,742 --> 00:00:26,482
I forget, it might be the Vishva Gosh's dictionary,
but one of the Sanskrit dictionaries...

6
00:00:26,597 --> 00:00:33,587
saying that 'depending upon one's
conception of self you can define atma'.

7
00:00:34,105 --> 00:00:42,205
So, there can be a context, where if someone is
in overwhelmingly badly concept of self,

8
00:00:42,248 --> 00:00:43,258
that's atma.

9
00:00:43,915 --> 00:00:46,225
Atma can also mean mind.

10
00:00:46,427 --> 00:00:48,587
Like in the Bhagavad-gita's sloka:

11
00:00:48,662 --> 00:00:51,587
uddhared ātmanātmānaṁ
nātmānam avasādayet

12
00:00:51,727 --> 00:00:58,587
ātmaiva hy ātmano bandhur
ātmaiva ripur ātmanaḥ
[Bg 6.5]

13
00:00:59,752 --> 00:01:02,362
Here atma can mean 'mind',

14
00:01:02,952 --> 00:01:07,672
it can mean 'the intelligence',
it can mean various things.

15
00:01:07,711 --> 00:01:10,051
The self, how you conceive of the self.

16
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:12,570
And the soul...

17
00:01:13,219 --> 00:01:17,219
But when we say 'soul',
again that's a general term.

18
00:01:18,578 --> 00:01:22,968
Like we're equating
consciousness and soul.

19
00:01:22,999 --> 00:01:27,919
'Consciousness' being a symptom
of the soul's presence.

20
00:01:29,644 --> 00:01:33,354
But then we have consciousness
in remembrance of Krishna,

21
00:01:33,377 --> 00:01:36,117
consciousness in forgetfulness of Krishna.

22
00:01:37,604 --> 00:01:41,604
So when we speak of the 'swarup',

23
00:01:42,936 --> 00:01:47,056
that means our, as you say,
spiritual body

24
00:01:47,785 --> 00:01:50,675
or our own actual spiritual self.

25
00:01:53,990 --> 00:02:04,760
That I've told before, that as we will take it
that this body is generated from exploiting tendencies.

26
00:02:06,277 --> 00:02:06,987
Right?

27
00:02:09,466 --> 00:02:12,746
jala-jana-nava lakhane stalavenksati

28
00:02:13,197 --> 00:02:15,247
It's mentioned in the Padma-purana:

29
00:02:15,284 --> 00:02:22,334
"By combinations of the three modes of nature,
you have millions of variations of lifeforms."

30
00:02:24,082 --> 00:02:25,722
So, the soul in delusion,

31
00:02:25,722 --> 00:02:30,014
the body is the biological expression of the soul's delusion,

32
00:02:30,237 --> 00:02:32,757
the outcome of exploiting tendencies.

33
00:02:33,156 --> 00:02:37,266
So you have all this millions of variations
upon this principle of exploitation:

34
00:02:38,264 --> 00:02:43,054
from gross exploitation to
subtle levels of exploitation.

35
00:02:43,370 --> 00:02:47,260
abrahma bhuvana loka punar avrtanorjuna

36
00:02:48,132 --> 00:02:49,962
This is mentioned in the...

37
00:02:50,535 --> 00:02:53,515
[sanskrit]
anyway...

38
00:02:53,633 --> 00:02:59,993
the 8th chapter of the Bhagavad-gita,
from Brahmaloka to the lowest positions.

39
00:03:00,654 --> 00:03:03,274
siva vrnchi amangalam

40
00:03:03,316 --> 00:03:04,846
It's mentioned in the Bhagavatam —

41
00:03:04,858 --> 00:03:07,408
even vrnchi, Bramha,

42
00:03:07,478 --> 00:03:11,758
there's some inauspiciousness
even in His world there.

43
00:03:11,956 --> 00:03:16,266
In the bodies on Brahmaloka, we find out
in the second canto of Srimad Bhagavatam,

44
00:03:17,122 --> 00:03:22,372
even the Brahma lives for
311 trillion years approximately.

45
00:03:22,606 --> 00:03:27,886
And the average of life spent on
Satyaloka's planets —15 trillion years.

46
00:03:27,930 --> 00:03:29,950
Still they have to die.

47
00:03:30,836 --> 00:03:40,656
So, the world of exploitation and
body's enabling exploiting tendencies.

48
00:03:40,764 --> 00:03:42,194
In Bhagavad-gita it says:

49
00:03:42,219 --> 00:03:45,889
āścarya-vat paśyati kaścid enam

50
00:03:46,097 --> 00:03:56,377
If you have a glimpse of your soul,
even in it's most elementary form,

51
00:03:56,426 --> 00:03:57,966
you'll be astonished.

52
00:03:58,168 --> 00:04:04,318
What to speak of having a glimpse
of its potential in the land of dedication.

53
00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:10,780
Sometimes Srila Guru Maharaj
would say to us from that perspective,

54
00:04:10,798 --> 00:04:14,228
he would say:
"Your future is so bright

55
00:04:15,211 --> 00:04:22,121
you can't imagine what awaits you,
if you can tend you're pursuing Krishna Consciousness."

56
00:04:22,144 --> 00:04:24,934
We haven't properly
conceived that.

